Voltage Stabilizers for Refrigerator Market Overview
The global Voltage Stabilizers for Refrigerator Market was valued at approximately USD 950 million in 2023 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 5.8% from 2023 to 2030, reaching a market value of USD 1.48 billion by 2030. The growth is driven by the rising need to protect refrigerators from voltage fluctuations, ensuring energy efficiency and enhancing appliance longevity.

Voltage stabilizers for refrigerators are critical in regions with frequent power surges. These devices ensure consistent voltage supply, reducing wear and tear on appliances. Emerging markets in Asia-Pacific, fueled by increasing urbanization and electricity access, contribute significantly to the market expansion.

